{"questionId":"12271","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;\">Given matrices <strong><em>A</em></strong><em>, <strong>B</strong>, <strong>C </strong></em>for which <strong><em>AB</em></strong><em> = <strong>C</strong> </em>and det <strong><em>A</em></strong> ≠ 0, express <strong><em>B</em></strong> in terms of <strong><em>A</em></strong> and <strong><em>C</em></strong><em>.</em></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Since det <strong><em>A</em></strong> ≠ 0, <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup>–1</sup>&nbsp;exists.&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1) </strong></em></p>\n<p>Hence <strong><em>AB</em></strong> = <strong><em>C</em></strong>&nbsp;⇒ <strong><em>B</em></strong> = <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup>–1</sup><strong><em>C&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(C1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12271","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.45a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given matrices A, B, C for which AB = C and det A ≠ 0, express B in terms of A and C.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}